      "name": "📖 HOW SHIFTS WORK - Explanation",
      "description": "SHIFT SCHEDULING EXPLAINED:\n\n1. **Shift Templates**: Define standard shift patterns (e.g., 'Morning 9AM-5PM', 'Night 10PM-6AM')\n   - Contains: name, start_time, end_time, break_duration\n   - Can have recurrence patterns (daily, weekly, monthly)\n\n2. **Employee Shift Assignments**: Assign templates to specific employees\n   - Links user_id to shift_template_id\n   - Has effective_from and effective_to dates\n   - Types: permanent, temporary, rotating\n   - Can override template times with custom_start/end times\n\n3. **Shift Timings**: Override branch opening/closing times\n   - Can apply to specific user (user_id) or entire branch (override_branch_id)\n   - Takes precedence over branch's default operating hours\n   - Used for: remote workers, flexible schedules, special arrangements\n\n4. **Schedule Requests**: Employees request changes\n   - time_off_request: Request day off\n   - schedule_change: Request different hours (come late/leave early)\n   - shift_swap: Swap shifts with colleague\n   - Requires manager approval\n\n5. **How Attendance Uses Shifts**:\n   - When employee checks in, system compares against their assigned shift\n   - Late: Check-in time > shift start_time + grace_period\n   - Early departure: Check-out time < shift end_time\n   - On-time: Within shift hours\n\n6. **Branch Hours vs Shift Hours**:\n   - Branch has opening/closing times (e.g., 8AM-6PM)\n   - Employee shifts can be within branch hours\n   - Shift timings can override branch hours for specific users\n   - Example: Branch opens 8AM, but security guard shift is 6PM-6AM (overnight)\n\n7. **Resume Late / Close Early**:\n   - Recurring shift assignments handle regular late starts\n   - Example: Employee comes at 10AM every Monday/Wednesday\n   - Create recurring shift with specific days and times"
